<div class="tool" data-tool="webrtc-leak-test">
  <p class="field-hint">
    WebRTC negotiates peer-to-peer connections by collecting the IP addresses
    your browser could use — including, on some setups, the real address a VPN
    is meant to hide. Nothing runs until you press the button: the test then
    opens one connection to a public STUN server to see which addresses come
    back.
  </p>

  <div class="action-row">
    <button id="rtc-run" class="btn btn-primary" type="button" disabled>Run the test</button>
    <button id="rtc-copy" class="btn btn-ghost" type="button" data-copy-target="#rtc-report" disabled>
      Copy results
    </button>
  </div>

  <p id="rtc-error" class="field-error" role="alert"></p>

  <div class="pane-group">
    <div class="pane-toolbar">
      <span class="pane-label">Verdict</span>
    </div>
    <div id="rtc-verdict" class="pane" aria-live="polite">
      Press <strong>Run the test</strong> to check what WebRTC reveals about your
      connection. JavaScript has to be enabled, and nothing leaves your device
      until you start the test.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="pane-group">
    <div class="pane-toolbar">
      <span class="pane-label">Public / externally-visible addresses</span>
    </div>
    <ul id="rtc-public" class="result-list" aria-live="polite">
      <li><span>Not tested yet</span></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="pane-group">
    <div class="pane-toolbar">
      <span class="pane-label">Local network addresses</span>
    </div>
    <ul id="rtc-local" class="result-list" aria-live="polite">
      <li><span>Not tested yet</span></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p class="field-hint">
    The one network request this page makes is the STUN connection to
    <code>stun.l.google.com:19302</code> named in the badge above. To confirm
    your normal public address for comparison, open the
    <a href="/tools/what-is-my-ip/">what is my IP</a> tool in another tab.
  </p>

  <!-- Plain-text report for the Copy results button (read live by clipboard.ts). -->
  <div id="rtc-report" hidden></div>
</div>

<script src="./client.ts"></script>
